    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "952fb51a_01367668",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 210,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-02T22:46:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we do not want to panic, just in case some middleware passes something other than a Flusher ResponseWriter?\n\nMaybe:\nflusher, hasFlusher :\u003d w.(http.Flusher)\nif !hasFlusher {\n  flusher \u003d nopFlusher{}\n}\n\n\n...\n\n\ntype nopFlusher struct{}\nfunc (nf nopFlusher) Flush() {}",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 210,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 210,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "c92b493af63635a347f4d03489608de1b95153ab",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "32ff8bba_d51a3c4b",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 210,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T17:02:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we definitely want to panic if a middleware passes a non-flushable ResponseWriter.  Because that means live-streaming logs would likely have otherwise been silently broken.\n\nFlushing was added in because if logs were streaming, and there were less that say 30 or so lines, nothing would show up until after the logs were done streaming.",
      "parentUuid": "952fb51a_01367668",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 210,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 210,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "c92b493af63635a347f4d03489608de1b95153ab",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "86071be6_09aebf6c",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 210,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-03T21:30:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Understood, but neither our middleware nor the ResponseWriter interface (and this handler) does not require it to be a Flusher. It is a violation of expectation to require that middleware conform to a non-explicit interface. I would recommend either:\n\n1) Update the router.Context to ensure that the ResponseWriter that is used must be a Flusher.\n\ntype ResponseWriter interface {\n  http.ResponseWriter\n  http.Flusher\n}\n\nThis would ensure that all of our middleware will propagate the Flusher interface.\n\nOr,\n\n2) Make it a soft failure (or maybe emit a warning log).\n\nI think asserting that our various, externally-defined middleware chains opt into an interface that is not enforced at compile-time is not a good direction.",
      "parentUuid": "32ff8bba_d51a3c4b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 210,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 210,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "c92b493af63635a347f4d03489608de1b95153ab",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
